casebody.data:
Jimmy PRATER, Appellant,
v.
Sean BRITZ and Christina Ann Britz and Britz Wrecking, Inc., Respondents. WD 81130 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: August 14, 2018 Phillip M. Murphy, II, Kansas City, MO, for appellant. Kelvin J. Fisher, Overland Park, KS, for respondent. Before Division Four: Karen King Mitchell, Chief Judge, Presiding, Cynthia L. Martin, Judge and Jeff Harris, Special Judge

ORDER

Per curiam:

Jimmy Prater appeals from the grant of summary judgment and of a motion to dismiss in favor of Sean Britz, Christina Britz, and Britz Wrecking, Inc. in a wrongful death action involving the death of Prater's father. Prater contends that the trial court erred in granting judgment in favor of the Respondents because there were genuine issues of material fact in dispute, and because the elements of collateral estoppel and judicial estoppel were not established. Prater also contends that the trial court erred in awarding costs to the Respondents.

Finding no error, we affirm. Rule 84.16(b).
